Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Bring a #medium pot{} of @salt{} water to a boil. Wash and dry produce.

Halve, peel, and dice @yellow onion{1/2}(peeled and diced) (whole onion for 4 servings). Finely dice @tomato{1}(finely diced). Trim @zucchini{1}(trimmed), then grate on the largest holes of a #box grater{}.

Once water is boiling, add @penne pasta{6%ounce} to #pot. Cook, stirring occasionally, until almost al dente, ~{8%minutes} (it'll finish cooking in the sauce step).

Drain penne. (Keep empty pot handy for sauce.)

Rinse @shrimp{10%ounce}(patted dry with paper towels and seasoned with salt and pepper) under cold water. Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add shrimp; cook, stirring occasionally, until cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} for shrimp. Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate. Wipe out pan.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @olive oil{4%tsp} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add diced onion, tomato, and a pinch of @salt{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until onion is softened, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Stir in @marinara cup{5%ounce}, zucchini, @veggie stock concentrate{2}, @tomato paste{1.5%ounce}, @Italian seasoning{1/2%tsp}, @water{3/4%cup}, @sugar{1.5%tsp}, additional olive oil, and @salt{}. Bring to a simmer; cook, stirring, ~{3%minutes} more. Turn off heat.

> For 4 servings, use 1 tsp Italian Seasoning, 1 1/2 cups water, 3 tsp sugar, 4 tsp olive oil, and 1 1/2 tsp salt.

Use pan used for shrimp here.

== Herbed Ricotta ==

While sauce simmers, in a #medium bowl{}, combine @ricotta cheese{4%ounce}, @Italian seasoning{1/2%tsp}, and a drizzle of olive oil. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> Use the rest of the Italian Seasoning as you like.

== Assembly ==

Add drained penne, sauce, and @butter{1%tbsp} to #pot used for pasta. Season with salt and pepper; stir to thoroughly combine.

Spread out half the pasta mixture in an #8-by-8-inch baking dish{}. (For 4, use a 9-by-13-inch baking dish.) Using a #tablespoon{}, dollop pasta mixture with herbed ricotta. Top with remaining pasta mixture, then sprinkle with @mozzarella cheese{1/2%cup}.

Stir shrimp into pot along with drained penne.

Cover #baking dish{} with #foil{}. Bake pasta on top rack for ~{10%minutes}, then remove from oven; discard foil.

Heat broiler to high. Broil until cheese is lightly browned, ~{4-5%minutes}.

> Watch carefully to avoid burning.

Let cool slightly; top with @?chili flakes{1%tsp} if desired. Divide between plates and serve.

> Shrimp are fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145º.